      <p>Your accommodation options depend on your legal situation, location and your needs.</p>

      <p>In most cases, your first port of call is to visit your council houing advice service. Drop in centres and other services can also support you to find accommodation - <a href="/find-help/support/?sub-category=housing">view our list of local housing advice services</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="h3">Accommodation Advice</h2>
      <p>To understand what options you have, and where to get support, <a href="/find-help/accommodation/advice/">read our advice guide</a>.</p>

      <h2 class="h3">Accommodation Listings</h2>
      <p>To browse all accommodation available in your area, by location and category, <a href="/find-help/accommodation/listing/">view our full listing</a>.</p>
      
      <h2 class="h3">More Information</h2>
      <p>For more detailed housing advice and legal support, you can also <a href="http://england.shelter.org.uk/get_advice">search Shelter's housing advice section</a>, or call their helpline on 0808 800 4444.</p>

